- title t 'welcome'

.jumbotron.text-center
  .row
    .col-md-7
      %h1 Ganban is a simple Kanban application

      %hr/

      - if current_user
        .row-fluid.marketing
          %p
            %strong Name:
            = current_user.name
            %br/
            %strong Email:
            = current_user.email
        - if @current_project
          = link_to 'Ganban Dashboard', @current_project, class: 'btn btn-lg btn-primary'
        - else
          = link_to 'Ganban Dashboard', new_project_path, class: 'btn btn-lg btn-primary'
      - else
        .sign-buttons
          = link_to 'Create your Kanban now!', new_user_registration_path, class: 'btn btn-lg btn-success'
          = link_to 'Sign in', new_user_session_path, class: 'btn btn-lg btn-primary'
        = link_to 'You can sign in as guest user from here<br/>(if you are in Rails Rumble Team)'.html_safe, agent_sessions_path(user_id: @guest_user.id), method: :post, class: 'sml-link'
    .col-md-5
      #preview
        =image_tag '0-ganban-preview.jpg'

.row
  .col-md-10.col-md-offset-1
    %p
      %h3 What is Kanban?
      %strong Kanban (かんばん(看板)?) (literally signboard or billboard)
      is a scheduling system for lean and just-in-time (JIT)
      production.Kanban is a system to control the logistical chain from a production point of view,
      and is not an inventory control system. Kanban was developed by Taiichi Ohno, at Toyota,
      to find a system to improve and maintain a high level of production.
      Kanban is one method through which JIT is achieved.


